Zach Randolph scored 21 points while Marc Gasol had 15 points and 10 rebounds for the Grizzlies, who shot 64.7 percent in the second half (22 of 34).

Dallas, which is seventh in the West, 4-1/2 games ahead of Oklahoma City, had a three-game winning streak halted. The Mavericks were led by Dirk Nowitzki and Devin Harris with 16 points each.

Golden State closed in on the best regular season record in franchise history by beating New Orleans 112-96.

